A 'Libellula saturata' is a species of dragonfly belonging to the family Libellulidae.
It has a bright red-brown color on its body, with darker patches on the wings and abdomen.
The wings are clear and veined, and the body is covered in fine hairs.
The eyes of the 'Libellula saturata' are large and dark, covering most of the head.
It can be found near streams, ponds, and other bodies of water across western North America.
The 'Libellula saturata' is known for its swift and agile flight, and can often be seen darting and hovering over the water surface.
It is an important predator, feeding on various insects including mosquitoes and smaller dragonflies.
